# Customer Purchase Prediction using Support Vector Machine (SVM)

This project demonstrates how to build a **Support Vector Machine (SVM) classification model** and deploy it using **Streamlit** to predict whether a customer will purchase a product.

The project covers the complete machine learning workflow including preprocessing, hyperparameter tuning, model evaluation, and deployment.

---

## Technologies & Libraries Used

- Python
- NumPy
- Pandas
- Matplotlib
- Scikit-learn
- Streamlit
- Pickle

---

## Dataset Description

The dataset contains customer information with the following columns:

- User ID
- Gender
- Age
- Estimated Salary
- Purchased (Target Variable)

Features used for model training:

- Age
- Estimated Salary

Target variable:

- Purchased (0 = No, 1 = Yes)

---

## Project Workflow

### 1. Data Loading
The dataset is loaded using Pandas and split into features (X) and target variable (y).

### 2. Train-Test Split
The dataset is divided into:

- 80% training data
- 20% testing data

This helps evaluate the model on unseen data.

---

### 3. Feature Scaling

StandardScaler is applied to normalize the feature values so that SVM performs effectively.

---

### 4. Hyperparameter Tuning

GridSearchCV is used to find the best model configuration.

Parameters tuned:

- C (regularization parameter)
- Kernel (linear, rbf, polynomial)
- Gamma (scale, auto)

The best combination of parameters is selected based on accuracy.

---

### 5. Model Evaluation

The trained model is evaluated using multiple metrics:

- Confusion Matrix
- Accuracy Score
- Precision
- Recall
- F1-score
- ROC Curve
- ROC-AUC Score

These metrics help measure classification performance.

---

### 6. Model Saving

The trained model and scaler are saved using **pickle**:

- svm_model.pkl
- scaler.pkl

This allows the model to be reused in the deployment application.

---

## Streamlit Application

An interactive Streamlit web app is built to make predictions using the trained SVM model.

### Features

- Upload CSV or Excel dataset
- Automatic prediction generation
- Display prediction results
- ROC curve visualization (if target column exists)
